Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @carrot{2}(coarsely grated), then coarsely grate (no need to peel). Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1%large}(chopped into small pieces). Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the carrot and onion to the pan and stir-fry until softened, ~{6-8%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{80%g}.

Once the veg has softened, add the chickpeas, garlic and @korma curry paste{50%g} to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @water{100%ml}. Bring to the boil and simmer until the chickpeas are tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir through the @mango chutney{40%g}, then remove from the heat. Using a #potato masher{}, roughly mash half the chickpeas in the pan until the sauce has thickened. Set aside and allow to cool slightly.

Unroll the @filo pastry sheets{4} (2 per person) and fold each sheet in half widthways to create a rectangle.

Spoon the mixture onto one end of each rectangle, leaving a 2cm border around the bottom 3 edges. Evenly sprinkle the cheese over the chickpea mixture.

Neatly fold both lengthway sides over the filling, then tightly roll them up like a burrito to enclose the filling.

Transfer the samosa rolls, seam-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}. Brush with a little @?oil{}, then bake on the top shelf until golden brown, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the tomatoes to the dressing and toss to coat.

Just before serving, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the tomato bowl. Toss to coat in the dressing.

> Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Share the veggie samosa rolls between your plates. Add a dollop of @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} for dipping.

Serve the tomato salad alongside. Enjoy!